A RESOLUTION
1 Proposing an amendment to the Constitution so as to authorize the General Assembly to
2 provide by law for the creation of a Children First Trust Fund; to provide for the
3 appropriation of moneys into such fund, including a one-time appropriation from the
4 Revenue Shortfall Reserve; to provide that moneys appropriated into such fund shall not
5 lapse and shall be used to provide scholarships, grants, or other forms of financial assistance
6 for child care services; to provide for the investment and reinvestment of a portion of the
7 moneys appropriated into such fund; to provide that returns on such investments shall be
8 used for financial assistance for child care services; to provide for related matters; to provide
9 for the submission of this amendment for ratification or rejection; and for other purposes.
10 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
11 SECTION 1.
12 Article III, Section IX, Paragraph VI of the Constitution is amended by adding a new
13 subparagraph to read as follows:
14 "(s) The General Assembly is authorized to provide by law for the creation of a Children
15 First Trust Fund for the purpose of providing, in accordance with the provisions of this
16 subparagraph, financial assistance for child care services in this state. Upon the creation
17 of such Children First Trust Fund, the General Assembly shall make a one-time
